visNetwork

visNetwork is a R package for network visualization, using vis.js javascript library

  • easy to use
  • custom shapes, styles, colors, sizes, â¦
  • works smooth on any modern browser for up to a few thousand nodes and edges
  • interactivity controls (zoom, physics, movement of nodes, tooltip)


Based on htmlwidgets, so :

  • compatible with shiny, R Markdown documents, RStudio viewer, R

Actually only available on DataKnowledge github

# for install visNetwork
devtools::install_github("dataknowledge/visNetwork")

Minimal example

visNetwork needs at least two informations :

  • a nodes data.frame, with id column
  • a edges data.frame, with from and to columns
nodes <- data.frame(id = 1:3)
edges <- data.frame(from = c(1,2), to = c(1,3))
visNetwork(nodes = nodes, edges = edges)

Simple individual nodes customization

  • Adding more variables on nodes data.frame. See visNodes for available options. 
nodes <- data.frame(id = 1:10, 
                    label = paste("Node", 1:10),                                 # add labels on nodes
                    group = c("GrA", "GrB"),                                     # control groups on nodes 
                    value = 1:10,                                                # control size adding value
                    shape = c("square", "triangle", "box", "circle", "dot", "star",
                    "ellipse", "database", "text", "diamond"),                   # control shape of nodes
                    title = paste0("<p><b>", 1:10,"</b><br>Node !</p>"),         # tooltip (html or character)
                    color = c("darkred", "grey", "orange", "darkblue", "purple"),# color
                    shadow = c(FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE, TRUE))                  # shadow
##   id  label group value    shape                     title    color shadow
## 1  1 Node 1   GrA     1   square <p><b>1</b><br>Node !</p>  darkred  FALSE
## 2  2 Node 2   GrB     2 triangle <p><b>2</b><br>Node !</p>     grey   TRUE
## 3  3 Node 3   GrA     3      box <p><b>3</b><br>Node !</p>   orange  FALSE
## 4  4 Node 4   GrB     4   circle <p><b>4</b><br>Node !</p> darkblue   TRUE
## 5  5 Node 5   GrA     5      dot <p><b>5</b><br>Node !</p>   purple   TRUE
## 6  6 Node 6   GrB     6     star <p><b>6</b><br>Node !</p>  darkred  FALSE
  • Numerous additional options are available(background/border/highlight color, position, font, scaling, level, â¦)

Simple individual edges customization

  • Adding more variables on edges data.frame. See visEdges for available options. 
edges <- data.frame(from = sample(1:10,8), to = sample(1:10, 8),
                    label = paste("Edges", 1:8),                                # add labels on edges
                    length = c(100,500),                                        # length
                    arrows = c("to", "from", "middle", "middle;to"),            # arrows
                    dashes = c(TRUE, FALSE),                                    # dashes
                    title = paste("Edge", 1:8),                                 # tooltip (html or character)
                    smooth = c(FALSE, TRUE),                                    # smooth
                    shadow = c(FALSE, TRUE, FALSE, TRUE))                       # shadow
##   from to   label length    arrows dashes  title smooth shadow
## 1    7  3 Edges 1    100        to   TRUE Edge 1  FALSE  FALSE
## 2    6 10 Edges 2    500      from  FALSE Edge 2   TRUE   TRUE
## 3    3  4 Edges 3    100    middle   TRUE Edge 3  FALSE  FALSE
## 4    9  2 Edges 4    500 middle;to  FALSE Edge 4   TRUE   TRUE
## 5   10  9 Edges 5    100        to   TRUE Edge 5  FALSE  FALSE
## 6    8  1 Edges 6    500      from  FALSE Edge 6   TRUE   TRUE
  • Numerous additional options are available(background/border/highlight color, font, scaling, â¦)

Global nodes/edges configuration

  • Set global options for nodes and edges using visNodes and visEdges, and use options per group using visGroups. 
nodes <- data.frame(id = 1:5, group = c(rep("A", 2), rep("B", 3)))
edges <- data.frame(from = c(2,5,3,3), to = c(1,2,4,2))

visNetwork(nodes, edges) %>% 
  visNodes(shape = "square") %>%                        # square for all nodes
  visEdges(arrow ="to") %>%                             # arrow "to" for all edges
  visGroups(groupname = "A", color = "darkblue") %>%    # darkblue for group "A"
  visGroups(groupname = "B", color = "red")             # red for group "B"

Global Options

Some global options are available in visOptions :

  • Highlight nearest (highlightNearest) nodes and edges clicking on a node, or selecting with a list (nodesIdSelection)
visNetwork(nodes, edges) %>% visOptions(highlightNearest = TRUE, nodesIdSelection = TRUE)

  • Data Manipulation (manipulation), and add a legend (legend)
visNetwork(nodes, edges, legend = TRUE) %>% visOptions(manipulation = TRUE)

Layout configuration

  • Layout (hierarchical or not) can be set with visLayout or visHierarchicalLayout (more parameters) :
visNetwork(nodes, edges) %>% visEdges(arrow = "to") %>% 
  visHierarchicalLayout() # same as   visLayout(hierarchical = TRUE)

Control interaction

You can control interaction with visInteraction :

  • enable/disable dragging nodes/network (dragNodes, dragView)
  • hide nodes/edges when dragging (hideEdgesOnDrag, hideNodesOnDrag)
  • enable/disable zoom (zoomView)
  • control hover colors (hover, hoverSelectedEdges)
  • use keyboard shortcut manipulation (keyboard)
  • enable multiselection (multiselect)
  • use navigation buttons (navigationButtons)
  • enable/disable selection (selectable)
  • control edges highlighting (selectConnectedEdges)
  • control tooltip delay (tooltipDelay)
  • Example : Relations between the characters of âLes miserablesâ
visNetwork(nodes, edges) %>% visInteraction(dragNodes = FALSE, hideEdgesOnDrag = TRUE, hover = TRUE) %>%
  visOptions(highlightNearest = TRUE, nodesIdSelection = TRUE)

And also

  • Physics options are available on visPhysics (solver and stabilization controls)
  • Use of javascript event with visEvents :
  • help for network configuration with visConfigure
  • some first clustering functionsâ¦ (visClusteringByColor, visClusteringByGroup)
visNetwork(nodes, edges) %>% visClusteringByGroup(groups = c("A","B")) %>%
  visEvents(zoom = "function(properties) {alert('zoom scale : ' + properties.scale);}")
